import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Effect_Amount_of_damage'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Effect_Amount_of_damage?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common Wildlife_Species involved in strikes?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts().max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts().max()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Cost_Total__'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Cost_Total__'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['Cost_Total__'].dropna(), vert=False, showfliers=True, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), whiskerprops=dict(color='black'), capprops=dict(color='black'), medianprops=dict(color='black'))
    ax.set_xlabel('Cost_Total__')
    ax.axvline(data['Cost_Total__'].mean(), color='red', label=f'Mean: {data["Cost_Total__"].mean():0.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['Cost_Total__'].median(), color='green', label=f'Median: {data["Cost_Total__"].median():0.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Cost_Total__?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'], density=True, alpha=0.5, color='blue', bins=20)

    ax.axvline(data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'].median()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Speed_IAS_in_knots during strikes?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
